1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,489
AI coding tools can produce an impressive first answer in seconds.

2
00:00:04,489 --> 00:00:08,017
But impressive is not the same as engineered.

3
00:00:08,017 --> 00:00:13,468
That first response may hide missed requirements, fragile error handling, weak accessibility, or code

4
00:00:13,468 --> 00:00:16,033
that becomes difficult to maintain.

5
00:00:16,033 --> 00:00:21,485
DevLoop AI changes the stopping point. It treats generation as the beginning of a

6
00:00:21,485 --> 00:00:23,409
visible engineering process.

7
00:00:23,409 --> 00:00:28,860
For every requirement, DevLoop plans the approach, generates a solution, reviews it, scores it,

8
00:00:28,860 --> 00:00:31,425
and improves it when needed.

9
00:00:31,425 --> 00:00:36,877
The application owns this loop. It stops when quality reaches eighty-five, or after a

10
00:00:36,877 --> 00:00:39,763
hard maximum of three reviewed iterations.

11
00:00:39,763 --> 00:00:43,611
Here is the deployed product running with OpenAI live.

12
00:00:43,611 --> 00:00:49,062
I am asking for a minimal Python project with packaging, source code, tests, Git

13
00:00:49,062 --> 00:00:51,627
ignore rules, and setup instructions.

14
00:00:51,627 --> 00:00:57,079
The interface exposes each stage as it happens: planning, generating, reviewing, and, when required,

15
00:00:57,079 --> 00:00:59,003
improving the result.

16
00:00:59,003 --> 00:01:04,454
The backend makes separate structured calls, validates every response, and streams progress to the

17
00:01:04,454 --> 00:01:07,019
Angular interface with server-sent events.

18
00:01:07,019 --> 00:01:12,471
This live result received an overall quality score of ninety-four on its first reviewed

19
00:01:12,471 --> 00:01:13,753
version.

20
00:01:13,753 --> 00:01:18,243
Because it already cleared the threshold, DevLoop stopped after iteration one.

21
00:01:18,243 --> 00:01:22,411
Stopping early here is expected behavior, not a missing loop.

22
00:01:22,411 --> 00:01:27,542
The result is scored across correctness, maintainability, security, accessibility, performance, and requirement coverage.

23
00:01:27,542 --> 00:01:32,993
Judges can inspect the plan, review findings, applied changes, generated output, and the exact

24
00:01:32,993 --> 00:01:36,841
stop condition instead of seeing only a final answer.

25
00:01:36,841 --> 00:01:42,293
The preview is correctly labelled Python, rather than displaying a fixed filename from another

26
00:01:42,293 --> 00:01:43,575
framework.

27
00:01:43,575 --> 00:01:47,744
For project-scaffolding prompts, DevLoop also returns a structured file manifest.

28
00:01:47,744 --> 00:01:50,951
This run produced six complete project files.

29
00:01:50,951 --> 00:01:56,402
The package can be downloaded as a ZIP for local inspection, while nested paths

30
00:01:56,402 --> 00:01:59,929
and unsafe filenames are validated before archive creation.

31
00:01:59,929 --> 00:02:05,381
The architecture stays intentionally focused: Angular for the experience, Express and TypeScript for orchestration,

32
00:02:05,381 --> 00:02:08,587
and OpenAI Structured Outputs for model responses.

33
00:02:08,587 --> 00:02:14,039
API keys remain on the server. Zod validates the model data, and the application—not

34
00:02:14,039 --> 00:02:16,604
the model—controls the iteration limit.

35
00:02:16,604 --> 00:02:22,055
Quality scores are structured model evaluations. DevLoop does not execute, compile, or security-audit generated

36
00:02:22,055 --> 00:02:23,338
code.

37
00:02:23,338 --> 00:02:28,789
That honest boundary keeps the project practical while making AI improvement transparent, measurable, and

38
00:02:28,789 --> 00:02:30,713
easy to demonstrate.

39
00:02:30,713 --> 00:02:36,165
DevLoop AI. Better first drafts come from visible engineering, because the first answer is

40
00:02:36,165 --> 00:02:38,089
just the beginning.

